snippet: President Viktor F. Yanukovich held his first face-to-face meeting with opposition leaders Friday as the country’s richest man, Rinat Akhmetov, expressed support for the demonstrators.
abstract: Ukrainian Pres Viktor F Yanukovich calls for end to protests at his first meeting with opposition leaders since outbreak of civil uprising; is under intense pressure to resolve crisis, from West and Russia, as well as from influential business men, known as oligarchs, who are increasingly worried about strife's effect on economy.
lead_paragraph: President Viktor F. Yanukovich held his first face-to-face meeting with opposition leaders Friday as the country’s richest man, Rinat Akhmetov, expressed support for the demonstrators.

headline.main: Meeting Opposition Leaders, Ukraine’s President Calls for End to Protests
headline.print_headline: Meeting Opposition Leaders, Ukraine’s President Calls for End to Protests
